<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,534,1720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,766,792]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[740,897,767,792]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophomilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polybapta">
<emphasis box="[740,897,767,792]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. polybapta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group but can be recognized by its pointed forewing with a deep incision before the apex. The wing coloration, unlike related species, is uniform rusty reddish-brown, slightly paler in basal part; wing pattern expressed by dark lines. In the female genitalia the species differs by having a moderately wide, funnel-shaped antrum with a deep central incision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,534,1720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,355,920,946]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[450,600,921,947]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="5.[151,273,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[191,1428,194,1729]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,194,1754]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Lophomilia spp., adults. 9. L. nekrasovi, male, holotype, Russia, Primorye terr., Khasansky distr., Slayanka (ZISP); 10. L. nekrasovi, female, paratype, Russia, Primorye terr., Khasansky distr., Sukhanovsky pass near Ryazanovka (IBSS); 11. L. rustica, male, holotype, China, Tapaishan (ZFMK); 12. L. rustica, female, paratype, same locality (ZFMK). 13. L. hoenei, male, holotype, China, Noth Yunnan, A-tun-tse (ZFMK); 14. L. hoenei, female, same locality, grey form (ZFMK); 15. L. hoenei, female, same locality, contrast form (ZFMK); 16. L. kogii, male, Russia, Primorye terr. Khasansky distr., Andreevka (FNM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274660/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs. 
<number box="[520,600,921,947]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="11.12">11, 12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[753,888,921,947]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="27.0" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="26.0">26–28 mm</quantity>
. Forewing with deep incision before pointed apex. Ground color of forewing uniform rusty reddish-brown; basal line hardly traceable. Antemedial line brown, more distinct in dorsal part of wing, weakly traceable and diffused in costal part; postmedial line arises on dorsum as black, oblique bar, narrowing to thin line beyond Cu 
<number box="[927,937,1037,1063]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1.0">1</number>
and extending to costa, bordered inside by dark brown suffusion, and outside by thin pale-brown line and brown suffusion; orbicular expressed as small black dot, reniform hardly traceable as pale spot; subterminal line diffuse, dentate, broken; terminal field with dark suffusion in apical part; cilia rusty-brown. Hindwing greyish-brown, slightly darker in terminal part, with weakly traceable diffused discal spot and blackish tornal spot; cilia yellowish-grey. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1139,1317,1191,1217]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1334,1422,1192,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 32" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[159,1436,174,1700]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,157,1717]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 32. Lophomilia spp., male genitalia. 29. L. nekrasovi, paratype, prep. 842 IBSS Russia, Primorye terr.; 30. L. rustica, paratype, China, Tapaishan, prep. 2086 VK ZFMK; 31. L. hoenei, China, Likiang, prep. 2101 VK ZFMK; 32. L. kogii, Russia, AM ZISP." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274663/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[1389,1422,1192,1218]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
). Uncus relatively thin, sickle-like, curved; tegumen higher than vinculum; juxta three-lobed; valva moderately long, with parallel margins; transtilla weak; costa well developed, in apical part separated from membranous valva; editum well expressed; clasper-harpe complex lies in longitudinal position, fused with costa, clasper with elongate sclerotized basal plate, harpe not expressed; sacculus small, sclerotised, with moderate flattened, stick-like extension, longer than half of valva; apical part of valva membranous, rounded, lobe-like; aedeagus relatively thin, moderate, with well expressed coecum, vesica large, bulbous, with three wide diverticula, with small patch of cornuti. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[636,847,1462,1488]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[865,955,1462,1488]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 49" captionStartId="18.[151,269,1778,1802]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,228,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,194,1754]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 49. Lophomilia spp. and Hepatica anceps, female genitalia. 40. L. flaviplaga, South Korea, prep. 250 - 2 d HL CIS; 41. L. takao, China, Yunnan, prep. VK NEFU; 42. L. diehli; paratype, prep. 6538 GB, Indonesia, Sumatra; 43. L. polybapta, China, China, Yunnan, prep. VK NEFU; 44. L. nekrasovi sp. n. China, Tapaishan, prep. 2032 VK ZFMK; 45. L. rustica, China, Tapaishan, prep. 2087 VK ZFMK; 46. L. hoenei, China, Yunnan, prep. 2102 VK ZFMK; 47. L. kogii, South Korea, prep. 231 - 2 c HL CIS; 48. L. albistria, prep. 6526 GB, Nepal, Kathmandu, Pulchouki Mt.; 49. H. anceps, South Korea, prep. 255 - 2 HL CIS." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274665/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[921,955,1462,1488]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor short, rather wide, papillae anales moderate, apophyses anteriores shorter than posterior ones, small, thin; antrum small, rather wide, funnel like; ductus bursae short, wide, flattened, sclerotized, in the region where it is joining with antrum membranous; corpus bursae rounded, elongate, with small signum in bottom part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,534,1720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,512,1616,1642]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Distribution and biology.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[529,618,1617,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 57" captionStartId="19.[151,269,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[192,1387,194,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,194,1948]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 57. Lophomilia spp., distribution maps. 50. L. flaviplaga; 51. L. takao; 52. L. polybapta; 53. L. nekrasovi; 54. L. rustica; 55. L. hoenei; 56. L. kogii; 57. L. albicosta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274666/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[585,618,1617,1643]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
). East and South 
<collectingCountry box="[826,900,1617,1643]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">China</collectingCountry>
. Probably multivoltine, adults collected from April to end of August. The larva and foodplant are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1174,1694,1720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,534,1720]" box="[197,1174,1694,1720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1694,1720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
